✅ Session 2026-06-18 (orchestrate spec arc: session-lever reconciliation + 3 new specs):
- **Reconciled token-efficiency spec with session-level levers.** Revision note on `SPEC-orchestrate-token-efficiency-2026-06-17`: a global `CLAUDE_CODE_SUBAGENT_MODEL=sonnet` (highest priority) OVERRIDES orchestrator-v2's per-task haiku routing (Explore/Bash/test → haiku), forcing cheap reads up to sonnet (~5× regression) — so do NOT set it globally; craft self-routes. Main-session `Workflow`+`budget` documented as a flow-level practice (not craft — commands can't call it). Default-engine decision rule: derivable spec → `:workflow`, parallel writes → `--swarm`, else fan-out; worktrees = isolation, not a token lever.
- **3 new specs on `dev` (all pushed):** `SPEC-orchestrate-decomposition-2026-06-18` (design RESOLVED — mode-scaled agent soft cap, single-concern + ≤K-file sizing, reuse confirm gate, one-shot planning, fan-out path only); `SPEC-orchestrate-swarm-2level-2026-06-18` (READY — `--swarm` takes optional level, default 1, `--swarm=2` for two levels; bottom-up convergence + per-level test gate + non-overlap guard); `RESEARCH-hierarchical-worktrees-2026-06-18` (nested-dir worktrees = git anti-pattern; real shape = hierarchical branches over flat sibling worktrees, cap 2).
- **Commits:** `711e5a2c` (reconciliation) → `0a432dc1` (decomposition) → `6618c469` (research) → `88de8b4f` (2-level swarm). flow-cli `1907aadb`: dropped `CLAUDE_CODE_SUBAGENT_MODEL` export. Implementation of all three deferred to worktrees (Next Action E).

✅ Session 2026-06-17 (token-efficiency spec/plan + quota tooling + scheduled cloud run):
- **Investigation → APPROVED spec + 16-task plan.** From "is orchestrate the token-usage culprit?" → finding: cost is `agents × inherited-context × turns`; prompt caching is the only structural discount; worktrees cost ZERO tokens (corroborated by Anthropic's published multi-agent numbers). `docs/specs/SPEC-orchestrate-token-efficiency-2026-06-17.md` (APPROVED) + sibling `SPEC-context-floor-hygiene-2026-06-17.md` (skeleton) + `SPEC-workflow-as-default-engine-2026-06-17.md` (SUPERSEDED). Plan `docs/plans/2026-06-17-orchestrate-token-efficiency.md` (16 TDD tasks). All commits pushed to `dev`.
- **Adversarial review earned its keep twice:** killed an infeasible "platform `Workflow()` engine" premise (craft dispatches via Task; no host Workflow tool callable from a command) → re-scoped to craft's real deterministic `:workflow` mode as default (parity-gated); and caught a stale-quota trap before it shipped into Phase Q.
- **Methodology hardened (user pref):** parity gate is estimation-based (effect sizes + 95% CI + surprisal, NO NHST/p-thresholds); cost-weighted metric (output 5×, cache_read 0.1×, cache_creation 1.25×); `.craft/` run-marker reuse (not `.flow/`).
- **Phase Q appended:** `/craft:quota` pre-flight gate (historical median+interval estimate vs LIVE rate_limits) advising SAFE/TIGHT/DEFER; flow-cli `dash` consumer is an out-of-scope producer/consumer follow-on.
- **Quota/limits question resolved:** the native statusline `rate_limits` field (5h/weekly % + resets, Pro/Max after first API response) is THE programmatic source — no public quota CLI/API exists (user's own archived feature-request confirms); claude-hud's Keychain→oauth/usage cache was stale (frozen March). Memory added: `claude-code-native-statusline-rate-limits`, `craft-no-platform-workflow-tool`, `stats-estimation-not-nhst`.
- **Scheduled a cloud routine** (`trig_017orFX3wJv4QborUvFGtvHS`, Mon Jun 22 09:00 MDT, sonnet-4-6) to implement the pure-code tasks (parser + estimator + persister) TDD-style and open a PR to `dev` — deliberately timed for AFTER the weekly quota reset (user on Max 20x; pacing heavy work around the window).

✅ Session 2026-06-15 (branch-guard draft=dev shipped + multi-surface-release spec/worktree):
- **PR #158 MERGED → dev** — `branch-guard.sh` now treats research `draft` as `dev` (smart protection: new code blocked, existing + `.md` + commits allowed, force/reset blocked). Bundled 5 bash regression cases (Group 2b) + 1 pytest auto-detect case (`test_repo_with_draft_protects_both`). Backs the `~/.claude/rules/draft-as-dev-research.md` rule directly — no more manual self-enforcement.
- **PR #159 MERGED → dev** — wired the branch_guard bash suites into `ci.yml`: new "Install branch-guard hook" step + "Run branch-guard bash suites" (`tests/test_branch_guard.sh` + `_e2e.sh`) with `SKIP_PERF=1` gating the 50-invocation timing test. branch_guard behavior is now CI-validated, not local-only.
- **Brainstorm + SPEC (approved): multi-surface release.** Read-only investigation of craft's plugin dev→release pipeline → `docs/specs/SPEC-multi-surface-release-2026-06-15.md` (`9df211ed`). Key finding: Claude **Code** and **Desktop/Cowork** use SEPARATE plugin registries; Desktop CAN subscribe to a custom GitHub marketplace by `owner/repo` (`addMarketplace`, same engine as Code) — so "one source → all surfaces" is achievable via the `marketplace.json` craft already ships + a one-time `claude plugin marketplace add`. Item 1 (Desktop spike) DONE; D1–D7 decisions + 6 work items.
- **Worktree scaffolded:** `feature/multi-surface-release` + `ORCHESTRATE-multi-surface-release.md` (5 phases: rforge drift fix, verify-surfaces engine, cache-prune, aggregator marketplace, docs). Impl pending a NEW worktree session (ORCHESTRATE-STOP rule).
- **Memory:** new `claude-desktop-vs-code-plugin-stores.md` (separate stores + addMarketplace) so the investigation isn't redone. Global rule `draft-as-dev-research.md` updated (hook now enforces draft=dev, PR #158).

